  "body": "Current version of the In Chat Messaging does not include any functionality for the options button.\r\n\r\nImplement this as these options are available on other screens.\r\n\r\nsee red square box in image:\r\n<img width=\"250px\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/22799766/8829dfed-25f7-4d73-b846-8e6b32868b98\" />\r\n\r\n\r\nThis should be implemented for the different variations, e,g 1-1, Group and Communities.\r\nThe individual actions can be implemented in follow up if this is too large or consider breaking this story into 3 separate tasks for each variation\r\n\r\nDesigns are here:\r\n\r\n1-1: https://www.figma.com/file/7KIYbhoqNGAIFonE0w9TDz/Messages-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=7365-512935&t=a5CFBvO6ImJoqxLC-4\r\n\r\n\r\nCommunities: https://www.figma.com/file/h9wo4GipgZURbqqr1vShFN/Communities-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=6301-422452&t=sHzSqc7SUJQNVVgm-4 \r\n\r\nFor communities a lot of these options already exist in: \r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/blob/develop/src/status_im2/contexts/communities/actions/community_options/view.cljs\r\n\r\nA similar approach could be taken or this functionality could be reused/extended",
